First, we express \(8\) and \(6\) in terms of modulo \(7\):
\[8 \equiv 1 \pmod{7} \implies 8^6 \equiv 1^6 \equiv 1 \pmod{7}\]
\[6 \equiv -1 \pmod{7} \implies 6^6 \equiv (-1)^6 \equiv 1 \pmod{7}\]

